{"course":"EDA 424","question_type":"mcq","question_text":"Krashen's Input Hypothesis states that language acquisition occurs when learners are exposed to input that is:","options":[{"option_text":"Slightly beyond the learner's current competence level (i+1) in a low-anxiety environment","is_answer":True},{"option_text":"Perfectly matched to the learner's current competence level with no new structures","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"Delivered exclusively through explicit grammar instruction and drills","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"Repeated identically until the learner achieves full memorization","is_answer":False}]},
