{"course":"EDA 424","question_type":"mcq","question_text":"The primary criticism of the Behaviourist theory of language learning is that it:","options":[{"option_text":"Cannot account for children's ability to produce novel grammatical sentences they have never heard before","is_answer":True},{"option_text":"Overestimates the role of innate grammatical knowledge in language acquisition","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"Ignores the role of the environment in shaping language behavior","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"Fails to explain how reinforcement affects language learning outcomes","is_answer":False}]},
