{"course":"EDA 424","question_type":"mcq","question_text":"Chomsky's concept of the Language Acquisition Device (LAD) suggests that:","options":[{"option_text":"Children are biologically predisposed to acquire language through an innate grammatical processing mechanism","is_answer":True},{"option_text":"Language is learned entirely through imitation and reinforcement from caregivers","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"Language acquisition depends entirely on the quality of formal instruction received","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"All languages are equally difficult to acquire regardless of the learner's age","is_answer":False}]},
{"course":"EDA 424","question_type":"mcq","question_text":"The Affective Filter Hypothesis by Krashen explains language acquisition failure in terms of:","options":[{"option_text":"High levels of anxiety, low motivation or low self-confidence creating a mental block against language input","is_answer":True},{"option_text":"Insufficient exposure to grammatical rules in formal language instruction","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"Neurological damage that prevents efficient language processing","is_answer":False},{"option_text":"Excessive use of the mother tongue interfering with target language development","is_answer":False}]},
